\strong{Optimal Weight Schemes}:
\itemize{
\item \strong{wts_BE_N}: Best Estimator using normal approximation
\item \strong{wts_APE_N}: Asymptotically Powerful Estimator using normal approximation
\item \strong{wts_BE_sparse}: Best Estimator using sparse mixture approximation
\item \strong{wts_APE_sparse}: APE using sparse mixture approximation
\item \strong{wts_equ}: Equal weights baseline (simple sum)
}

The final Fisher p-value is from the equal weights row (last row).

\strong{When Fisher Test is Optimal}:
\itemize{
\item Causal variants have mixed effect directions (some positive, some negative)
\item Effect sizes have moderate heterogeneity (less extreme than SKAT scenario)
\item Combines benefits of Burden and SKAT approaches
\item More robust than Burden when effect directions are mixed
\item More powerful than SKAT when effects are moderately homogeneous
